video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Main port wound creation - 2 or 3 plane wound insertion created temporally  2 plane insertion: Angle blade upwards slightly first then insert blade horizontally into anterior chamber
instrument_used: Keratome   +/- Conj forceps to stabilise eye

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Viscoat insertion

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Insertion of a pupil-dilating agent?

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Creation of anterior capsulotomy  Begin at 9 oc  Tear the anterior capsule clockwise  To create a round capsulorhexis  Regrasp the tearing flap at 3 and 6 oc  Around 5.5mm in diameter

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Insert cannula tip under anterior capsule and insert BSS to separate lens from capsule   Signs of hydrodissection Wave  Nucleus lift  Nucleus prolapse

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Divide and conquer technique  Creation of trough - using phaco probe to create a central groove in the lens nucleus till it is deep enough to crack  A gauge of the depth is to be able to see a hint of the fundal red reflex  Phaco memory 1 setting
instrument_used: Phaco probe   Second instrument - chopper, splitter, mushroom

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Cracking of lens nucleus into 2 halves Place two instruments deep into the groove and separate the pieces horizontally
instrument_used: Phaco probe   Second instrument - chopper, splitter, mushroom

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Stop and chop Switch to phaco memory 2 setting (higher vacuum) Phaco probe holds the piece and 2nd instrument chops the lens half into smaller fragments  The small fragments are removed by the phaco probe
instrument_used: Phaco probe   Second instrument - chopper, splitter, mushroom

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Main port creation at 3 oc position
instrument_used: Keratome   +/- Conj forceps to stabilise eye

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Insert viscoat to fill the capsular bag

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Load lens into cartridge

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Use injector to insert lens into capsular bag   +/- sinksy hook to stabilise the eye and provide counter traction

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Rotate the lens into the capsular bag

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Use I/A probe to aspirate viscoat from bag and angles of the eye

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Hydrate the side port and main port wounds using BSS cannula  Creating a whitish haze around the sides of the wounds

video_title: CataractCoach 1245: tips to improve your phaco technique
detailed_steps: Check eye pressure  Use side of BSS cannula to lightly depress onto eye to assess the intraocular pressure If too firm, release some fluid from the side or main port wound
